==Abstract==

A PAIcoin Development Proposal (PDP) is a design document providing information to the PAIcoin community, or describing a new feature for PAIcoin or its processes or environment. The PDP should provide a concise technical specification of the feature and a rationale for the feature.

We intend PDPs to be the primary mechanisms for proposing new features, for collecting community input on an issue, and for documenting the design decisions that have gone into PAIcoin. The PDP author is responsible for building consensus within the community and documenting dissenting opinions.

Because the PDPs are maintained as text files in a versioned repository, their revision history is the historical record of the feature proposal.

